      "content": "a \"misconfigured data storage issue\" still sounds like we messed up, which is what we're trying to avoid. if a tech journalist asks specifically if any sensitive info was exposed or if it was an error in our security protocols, how do we answer that without sounding like we're hiding something? is there a way to tie this into something proactive, like a system update or a scheduled migration?",
